# AgentCodex

AgentCodex is a Codex-first project that integrates:

- `everything-claude-code` (ECC) as the operational baseline for Codex
- `agentspec` as the domain and workflow layer for spec-driven data engineering

The goal is to produce a Codex-native framework that preserves the best parts of AgentSpec:

- 5-phase SDD workflow
- domain-specific agents for data engineering
- KB-first execution
- explicit routing and escalation

while replacing Claude-only assumptions with Codex-native surfaces:

- `AGENTS.md` instead of `CLAUDE.md`
- `.codex/config.toml` and role configs instead of Claude plugin manifests
- Codex multi-agent roles instead of Claude slash-command/plugin wiring
- instruction-based governance instead of Claude hooks

As of April 22, 2026, AgentCodex also contains a raw upstream import layer under `.agentcodex/imports/` with material copied from both source frameworks for direct reuse and gradual normalization.

Architectural decisions are recorded repo-locally under [docs/adr](/home/user/Projetos/agentcodex/docs/adr:1).

