Bootstrap a real project with the preferred Codex-first flow:

```bash
agentcodex install /path/to/your-project
```

Bootstrap a project with a maturity profile overlay:

```bash
agentcodex install /path/to/your-project --profile agentic-llm
```

Use `init` only when you explicitly want the scaffold without a local `.codex/` base:

```bash
agentcodex init /path/to/your-project
```

Check a bootstrapped project:

```bash
agentcodex check-project /path/to/your-project
```

Generate a project-standard readiness report:

```bash
agentcodex readiness-report /path/to/your-project
```

Enforce the project-standard ship gate:

```bash
agentcodex ship-gate /path/to/your-project
```

Evaluate the executable Maturity 5 DataOps + LLMOps baseline:

```bash
agentcodex maturity5-check /path/to/your-project --profile data-platform
```

Refresh all generated AgentCodex artifacts after changes:

```bash
agentcodex refresh-all
```

This now also:

- regenerates `docs/STATUS.md`
- synchronizes feature context histories in `.agentcodex/history/` when workflow artifacts exist

Refresh everything and also synchronize/check a target project:

```bash
agentcodex refresh-all --target-project /path/to/your-project --with-codex
```

Synchronize a project and refresh its active maturity profile overlay:

```bash
agentcodex sync-project /path/to/your-project --profile regulated-enterprise
```

Refresh trusted public source metadata for the KB control plane:

```bash
agentcodex sync-sources --apply
```

When sandbox network limits block upstream access, run the command outside sandbox limits so the registry lock, summaries, and retrieval index reflect real upstream state.

Install repo-local automation hooks for this repository:

```bash
agentcodex install-local-automation
```

Prepared hooks:

- `.githooks/pre-commit` -> `agentcodex refresh-all --skip-import-catalog`
- `.githooks/post-commit` -> `agentcodex refresh-all`

Retrieve compact long-term memory context from the local memory slice:

```bash
agentcodex memory-retrieve "project-standard ship gate" --task-type review --scope project --scope-value agentcodex
```

Write a new local memory payload:

```bash
agentcodex memory-ingest semantic /path/to/memory.json
```

Compact local memory snapshots:

```bash
agentcodex memory-compact
```

Validate memory schemas and checked payloads:

```bash
agentcodex memory-validate
```

Access-aware retrieval example:

```bash
agentcodex memory-retrieve "project-standard ship gate" --scope project --scope-value agentcodex --requester-role reviewer --json
```

Retrieval packets now include:

- `access_denials`
- `retention_filtered`

Check backend health explicitly:

```bash
agentcodex memory-health mem0 --json
agentcodex memory-health qdrant --json
```

Memory operations now also emit local observability artifacts under:

- `.agentcodex/observability/logs/`
- `.agentcodex/observability/runs/`
- `.agentcodex/observability/metrics/memory-health.json`
- `.agentcodex/observability/failures/memory-failures.json`

Memory-specific roles now also exist:

- `memory-architect`
- `memory-governance-engineer`
- `memory-observability-engineer`

Memory routing is now also explicit:

- memory design and semantic/episodic/procedural architecture -> `memory-architect`
- memory retention, ownership, sensitivity, and access policy -> `memory-governance-engineer`
- memory metrics, tracing, hit rate, failures, and access denials -> `memory-observability-engineer`

Memory-oriented file hints now include:

- `.agentcodex/memory/**/*`
- `.agentcodex/cache/memory/**/*`
- `.agentcodex/reports/memory/**/*`

Memory tests now exist under:

- `.agentcodex/tests/memory/`

Run them with:

```bash
python3 -m unittest discover -s .agentcodex/tests/memory -p 'test_*.py'
```

Memory final reports now also exist under:

- `.agentcodex/reports/memory/implementation-report.md`
- `.agentcodex/reports/memory/risk-report.md`
- `.agentcodex/reports/memory/test-report.md`

`check-project` now validates:

- required managed directories and files
- command procedure bundle presence and minimum section structure
- template bundle presence and minimum content markers
- routing manifest shape
- expected KB index domains
- extra local commands, templates, and KB domains as non-blocking notes

Refresh AgentCodex-managed files in an existing project:

```bash
agentcodex sync-project /path/to/your-project
```

Refresh managed files and `.codex/` together:

```bash
agentcodex sync-project /path/to/your-project --with-codex
```

`sync-project` now reports managed drift before overwriting files:

- `missing` for managed files or domains not present in the target
- `outdated` for managed content that differs from the AgentCodex source
- `extra` for local project additions that are not part of the managed bundle

Extras are reported but not deleted automatically.

The bootstrap now creates:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `.agentcodex/PROJECT_AGENTSCODEX.md`
- `.agentcodex/features/DEFINE_EXAMPLE_PROJECT_FEATURE.md`
- `.agentcodex/commands/*`
- `.agentcodex/templates/*`
- `.agentcodex/routing/routing.json`
- `.agentcodex/kb/*`
- `.agentcodex/features/example-project-standard/*`

The example feature scaffold under `.agentcodex/features/example-project-standard/` is the current reference implementation of the AgentCodex Project Standard.
Its authoritative manifest lives at [project-standard.json](/home/user/Projetos/agentcodex/.agentcodex/project-standard.json:1).

For projects that should be born at a stronger operating bar, AgentCodex also exposes an executable baseline in [maturity5-baseline.json](/home/user/Projetos/agentcodex/.agentcodex/maturity/maturity5-baseline.json:1).
This baseline builds on the Project Standard plus control-plane checks instead of replacing them.
Current profiles:
- `data-platform`
- `agentic-llm`
- `regulated-enterprise`

When a profile is selected during `init` or `sync-project`, AgentCodex also applies a profile-specific overlay under `.agentcodex/ops/` and writes `.agentcodex/maturity/ACTIVE_PROFILE.md`.

`check-project` now also understands this standard semantically:

- the reference scaffold can remain placeholder-heavy and is reported through notes
- any real feature folder that includes `CHECKLIST.md` is treated as a strict project-standard target
- required artifacts must exist
- key artifacts must satisfy required markers declared in `.agentcodex/project-standard.json`
- blocks marked not applicable must be justified explicitly in the corresponding artifact

## Manifest Generation

Use the CLI commands above to regenerate role and routing manifests.

## Verification

The local validator currently checks:

- routing manifest structure and referenced roles
- KB index and required KB files
- roles manifest integrity
- command procedure structure and references
- workflow docs, templates, and command index consistency
- import manifest integrity
- text hygiene on the distributed AgentCodex surface
- project-standard scaffold presence and semantic readiness rules for real feature folders

## Local KB Status

The local KB is no longer only quick-reference material.

Expanded domains now include local `concepts/` and `patterns/` content:

- `dbt`
- `data-quality`
- `orchestration`
- `spark`
- `airflow`
- `sql-patterns`
- `lakehouse`
- `streaming`
- `terraform`
- `ai-data-engineering`
